node.text:
The restaurants have ITC have always been a favourite at home. Whether it is Dakshin at @itcwindsor , Edo at @itcgardenia and more. ‚Å£
‚Å£
And we have been missing the warmth of ITC, the delicious food and more. But now there is a way to experience it all at home to the extent possible. With Gourmet Couch, a unique takeaway and delivery service by @itchotels . Delicious handpicked options from the best of their restaurants. Sealed with a ‚Äúwe assure‚Äù seal which is an assurance from the ITC group for the most stringent hygiene standards being followed. ‚Å£
‚Å£
We thoroughly enjoyed our indulgent meal from Kebabs & Kurries. Everything was delicious but the mango phirni just took the cake. ‚Å£
‚Å£
If you want a celebration meal this weekend, order via ITC. After all, we can all do with a bit of celebration now. ‚Å£A special mention for completely bio degradable packing. Some like Biryani actually came in a ceramic bowl. 
‚Å£
Thanks @iamsimonti for sending this. ‚Å£
‚Å£

‚Å£
Text Update - So end of last week when I realised I might need a COVID test, there was so much confusing information on the internet. A few folks here helped me figure it out and paying it forward by sharing with my experience. Also a disclaimer, this thread is of people of our strata somewhat. I didn't explore getting tested in BBMP centres so that is the information I don't have. Please don't @ me pointing my privilege, I am aware of it already. ‚Å£
‚Å£
Private hospitals have set up something called a "Fever/Flu Clinic". That is where you go as your first POC. The list of hospitals that I figured who have this are ‚Å£
1. Manipal Hospital ‚Å£
2. Columbia Asia‚Å£
3. Sakra ‚Å£
4. Apollo‚Å£
‚Å£
We picked Columbia Asia from the lot, simply because of two reasons. ‚Å£
1. Closer to home ‚Å£
2. We felt it would be less crowded than others (especially Manipal, where I have heard the queues are longer)‚Å£
‚Å£
The Columbia Asia flu clinic is set up next to the ER and I personally found it very efficient. It took me one hour from entry to exit including basic checks, doctor consultation & the actual test.  The process is fairly simple. ‚Å£
1. You check in & pay‚Å£
2. A doctor tests your vitals including fever, O2 Saturation, BP, pulse etc. Records your symptoms ‚Å£
3. You consult the doctor who takes your travel history, checks some more on symptoms. ‚Å£
4. Prescribes the test if needed‚Å£
‚Å£
Contd in comments - ‚Å£

Deserted‚Å£
Beautiful ‚Å£
Healing‚Å£
‚Å£
The video literally took my breath away. This is a city I LOVE. This is a city I moved to 18 yrs ago. This is my city ‚ù§Ô∏è‚ù§Ô∏è‚Å£
‚Å£
Video created by BBMP. ‚Å£
‚Å£
Share with everyone you know and pause to think how can we continue to keep Bangalore this glorious always. ‚Å£
‚Å£
#sinamon #bangalore ‚Å£

#TogetherAtHome #CookTogetherAtHome Yesterday was a bad day, I felt overwhelmed by all the news floating around me. I felt the anxiety creeping in and talking over my sane self. But I know we can‚Äôt let that happen. We need to stay sane, positive and at home for the foreseeable future.‚Å£
‚Å£
I knew I had to turn this around, for me and for the little stuff I can do from my own end. It might be a small thing but hey every drop matters. For the next 10-15 days, I promise to share a recipe everyday here (with a lot of help from @nivichengs). ‚Å£
‚Å£
Me and her are also here to help you with what can you cook. If you have ingredients at home and don‚Äôt know what to cook, leave a comment in this video and will send you a recipe/meal ideas for the same. I will also keep a story question running for this for the next 7 days continuously. So at any time you are stuck, please enter in that and we will provide suggestions. ‚Å£
‚Å£
I am also hereby urging you all to you cook and share recipes, do spread the happiness and positivity around and make staying at home easier. To start with tagging some of my favourite food people for this. @rushinamg @finelychopped (who is coming up with something interesting too, stay tuned), @therdplife @cupcakeree @pikturenama @skoranne ‚Å£
‚Å£
So let‚Äôs share the love of food while we are at home. Tag me and #TogetherAtHome #CookTogetherAtHome  and I promise to share all recipes in my stories <3 ‚Å£
‚Å£
Let‚Äôs beat #COIVD with love and food people. ‚Å£

Also saree from @chhapa_gj8 üíì

node.text:
The regular readers here know that inspite of the fact that I am often lowcarbing, bread is my achilles heel. I love a good bread and I find it very hard to say no to a good sandwich. ‚Å£
‚Å£
Today in my stories I shared the recipe of comforting yet strangeish sandwich I first had about 18 odd years ago as a person who had just moved to Bangalore. There was a ‚ÄúJuice Junction‚Äù near office which had ‚ÄúChanna Masala Sandwich‚Äù on the menu. I think I ordered it part because of curiosity and partly because I was missing home and channa üò¨ What came was nothing I had imagined but it comforted a girl longing for home. It became a regular order for me then. ‚Å£
‚Å£
I haven‚Äôt gone to a Juice Junction in years now but I still make some version of this sandwich often. Especially when I am longing for those easy carefree times. ‚Å£
‚Å£
Recipe is fairly easy - cook leftover channa till dry, mash them up. Add chutney/chilli sauce/hung curd/mayo to bread. Add mashed up channa, cheese and grill till brown. ‚Å£
‚Å£
Make this and share a picture people? ‚Å£
‚Å£
Also share your favourite comforting or strangeish sandwich combos? Maybe I will try them all and tag you when I do ;) ‚Å£
‚Å£

It‚Äôs been 19 months of any sort of excitement and adventure in life. Yes, we have taken some small breaks but we were desperately looking for doing something this summer which is safe (as much as it can be) and yet takes our mind from the routine and makes us feel alive. And it‚Äôs the road that makes all three of us alive. We were anyways going to make a trip to Delhi and decided to drive down rather than flying. ‚Å£
‚Å£
And by God, the BEST decision we have taken in a while inspite of the fact that I had serious apprehensions about being in a car for 3 days with family again ü§¶üèΩ‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏èüòÇ‚Å£
‚Å£
A total of 2200kms , 25hrs of driving approximately. SO MUCH FUN!!!! We broke our journey in three stops‚Å£
1. Hyderabad , stayed at Hyatt (about 580kms & 7hrs) ‚Å£
2. Jhansi, stayed at LemonTree (1710kms total from start, 1130km for that day, 13hrs). This was our best day. Car was on a song, we were in our elements and were beating Google ETA like nobody‚Äôs business ‚Å£
3. Home (2172kms total, 472kms for that day, 6 hrs). Agra-Delhi expressway is a beauty but please fuel up before you enter it. We had a bit of drama while on it üò¨‚Å£
‚Å£
We mostly packed food as snacks like theplas, bread etc for our meals. Also got the hotels we stayed at to pack meals for the road. And stopped on the highway in open non crowded places only a few times for chai etc.‚Å£
‚Å£
This was just what our soul needed honestly. Now 2 weeks in Delhi and then the return journey awaits, which we are equally excited about. ‚Å£
‚Å£
Folks, take all precautions, mask up, take the vaccine and then start doing the small things that make you happy ‚ù§Ô∏è‚Å£
‚Å£
